title: Issa Rae Still Feels 'Insecure' Sometimes
text: Best Dressed at the 2017 Golden Globes Advertisement - Continue Reading Below Rae explained her discomfort as "just being in a place of constantly wondering what people think and how they think. I've gotten better about that. It's just rooted in feeling out of place. I feel like, 'Oh wow, I made something from scratch and it's out there.' So when it comes to work, I can feel confident. But my social lifeâ€“it is what it is at this point." Asked if the Issa character we see on the show is the same as the real-life version, she said, "We're kind of the same. I feel like I'm later in her stage. I know myself a lot more. I'm more honest with myself than she is. So she has a lot more going through, as do I, but I'm further along on the journey than she is. She's probably me like eight years ago."
